data.enText: means

data.chText: 方式；方法；途径
data.enText: an action, an object or a system by which a result is achieved; a way of achieving or doing sth

data.chText: 电视是一种有效的通信手段。
data.enText: Television is an effective means of communication.

data.chText: 有没有什么办法和他取得联系？
data.enText: Is there any means of contacting him?

data.chText: 你有没有任何身份证件？
data.enText: Have you any means of identification ?

data.chText: 我们需要赶往伦敦，但却没有任何交通工具。
data.enText: We needed to get to London but we had no means of transport .

data.chText: 财富；钱财
data.enText: the money that a person has

data.chText: 人们应该按照各自的负担能力来消费。
data.enText: People should pay according to their means .

data.chText: 他无钱养活妻小。
data.enText: He doesn't have the means to support a wife and child.

data.chText: 私立学校的费用是大多数人无力支付的。
data.enText: Private school fees are beyond the means of most people (= more than they can afford).

data.chText: 这样按月还钱，你能承受得了吗？
data.enText: Are the monthly repayments within your means (= can you afford them) ?

data.chText: 要尽可能量入为出。
data.enText: Try to live within your means (= not spend more money than you have).

data.chText: 有钱人
data.enText: a man of means (= a rich man)
by all means

data.chText: 可以；当然行；没问题
data.enText: used to say that you are very willing for sb to have sth or do sth

data.chText: “我看一眼行吗？”“当然可以。”
data.enText: ‘Do you mind if I have a look?’ ‘By all means.’
by means of sth

data.chText: 借助…手段；依靠…方法
data.enText: with the help of sth

data.chText: 重物是用起重机吊起来的。
data.enText: The load was lifted by means of a crane.
by no means
not by any (manner of) means

data.chText: 绝不；一点也不
data.enText: not at all

data.chText: 她绝不是个毫无经验的教师。
data.enText: She is by no means an inexperienced teacher.

data.chText: 我们离成功还远着呢。
data.enText: We haven't won yet, not by any means.
a means to an end

data.chText: （本身并不重要或有趣的）达到目的的手段
data.enText: a thing or action that is not interesting or important in itself but is a way of achieving sth else

data.chText: 他不怎么喜欢这项工作，只是把它看作达到目的的手段而已。
data.enText: He doesn't particularly like the work but he sees it as a means to an end.
the end justifies the means

data.chText: 只要目的正当，可以不择手段
data.enText: bad or unfair methods of doing sth are acceptable if the result of that action is good or positive
by fair means or foul

data.chText: 不择手段
data.enText: using dishonest methods if honest ones do not work
ways and means

data.chText: （做某事现有的）方法和资源，手段和财力
data.enText: the methods and materials available for doing sth

data.chText: 筹资办法
data.enText: ways and means of raising money

word_means: mean的第三人称单数和复数

means: mean的第三人称单数和复数

ex.enText: His teaching method is quite traditional.

ex.chText: 这是中国学生学好英语的一种有效的方法。
ex.enText: This is an effective method for Chinese students to learn English well.

synonyms.bx: 指有计划地做某事的方法，尤指很多人都知道并使用的方法。

ex.chText: 他的新英语教学法很受学生欢迎。
ex.enText: His new approach to teaching English was very popular among the students.

ex.chText: 你为什么不采用传统的艺术评论方法呢？
ex.enText: Why don't you take a traditional approach to art criticism?

synonyms.bx: 指行事或处理问题的方法，常后接介词 to 。

ex.chText: 他像往常那样结束了讲话。
ex.enText: He finished the speech in his usual manner.

ex.chText: 他以这种方式死去，使得该事件更加复杂了。
ex.enText: The manner of his death made the matter more complicated.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事或某事发生的方式，通常只用单数。

ex.chText: 这是他们唯一的交流方式。
ex.enText: This is their only means of communication.

ex.chText: 体罚不应该作为约束儿童的手段。
ex.enText: Physical punishment should not be used as a means of controlling children.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事或为达到某种目的而采用的方法或手段。

ex.chText: 他们有不同的思维方式。
ex.enText: They have different modes of thought.

ex.chText: 她当时期待着过一种悠闲的生活。
ex.enText: She was looking forward to a relaxed mode of life.

synonyms.bx: 指行为、生活或做某事的方式，多因习惯、传统或习俗而形成，有时含刻板之意。

ex.chText: 你处理这个问题的方式是什么？
ex.enText: What is your way to tackle this problem?

ex.chText: 游泳是减肥的一种方式。
ex.enText: Swimming is one way to lose weight.

ex.chText: 他用他自己的方式爱她。
ex.enText: He loved her in his own way.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指做某事或达成某事的方法，也可指某事发生的方式。

tr: how a result is obtained or an end is achieved
example: an example is the best agency of instruction

tr: an instrumentality for accomplishing some end

example: he is a man of means

value.def: A means of doing something is a method, instrument, or process which can be used to do it. Means is both the singular and the plural form for this use.

example.ex: The move is a means to fight crime...
example.tran: 采取这项举措是为了打击犯罪。

example.ex: The army had perfected the use of terror as a means of controlling the population...
example.tran: 军队已经深谙利用恐怖手段控制民众之道。

example.ex: Business managers are focused on increasing their personal wealth by any available means.
example.tran: 企业经理一心只想用尽办法增加个人财富。

value.tran: 方法;手段;工具(means 用于此意时单复数同形)

value.def: You can refer to the money that someone has as their means .

example.ex: He did not have the means to compensate her.

value.def: If someone is living beyond their means, they are spending more money than they can afford. If someone is living within their means, they are not spending more money than they can afford.

example.ex: The more gifts she received, the more she craved, until he was living beyond his means...
example.tran: 得到的礼物越多，她的胃口就越大，直到他捉襟见肘为止。

example.ex: It is far better to pay off old debts steadily by living within your means.
example.tran: 量入为出地一步步偿还旧债，这个方法要好得多。

value.tran: 超出财力；入不敷出/在财力之内；量入为出

value.def: If you do something by means of a particular method, instrument, or process, you do it using that method, instrument, or process.

example.ex: This is a two year course taught by means of lectures and seminars...
example.tran: 本课程为期两年，授课形式为讲座与研讨。

example.ex: The trailer was connected to the car by means of a complicated system of hoses, pipes and rods.
example.tran: 活动房屋通过一系列复杂的软管、管道和连杆与汽车相连。

value.def: You can say 'by all means' to tell someone that you are very willing to allow them to do something.

example.ex: 'Can I come and have a look at your house?' — 'Yes by all means'.
example.tran: “我可以过来看看你的房子吗？”“当然可以。”

value.def: You use expressions such as 'by no means', 'not by any means', and 'by no manner of means' to emphasize that something is not true.

example.ex: This is by no means out of the ordinary...
They were not finished, however, not by any means.
example.tran: 不过，他们并没有结束,绝对没有。

gramarinfo.label: PHR with cl/group, PHR before v

value.tran: 决不;丝毫不;一点儿也不

value.def: If you say that something is a means to an end, you mean that it helps you to achieve what you want, although it may not be enjoyable or important itself.

example.ex: We seem to have lost sight of the fact that marketing is only a means to an end.
example.tran: 我们似乎忽略了这样一个事实：营销只是达到目的的手段。
